MissionCommands.Message: Okay, Jack. It looks like O2 tank 1 pressure is just a hair over 200.
We confirm that here and the temperature also confirms it.
Okay. Does it look like it's still going down?
It's slowly going to zero, and we're starting to think about the LM lifeboat.

Yes. That's what we're thinking about, too. You want me to do a quick P52? It kind of looks like - We've been talking it over, and it kind of looks like we'd probably align our plats - LM platform with our platform and then power down the CM, and keep the LM powered up doing a DPS - whatever DPS burns you give us?

13, we're not going to concern ourselves at the moment with a DPS burn. It's going to be some time before we'd get to that; but we're working on other procedures to give you, which will allow us to use the LM systems. Over.
Okay. Real fine.
Apollo 13, Houston. We'd like to charge battery A now.
Charge battery A. Roger.
[Follow the SYSTEM: EPS > BATTERY CHARGING to charge Battery A, press ROGER when complete]

And, Jack, in regards to your question about the P52 and LM platform, it's - There's no need to worry about that now. We wouldn't be using the LM platform for - until about 79 hours, so let's go as is on the platform for now. Over.
Okay. We understand.
And, Jack, we've turned off the waste dump heater. If you're going to consider dumping any more waste water, we probably ought to do it while the duct is warm there.
Okay, Jack. Let's keep the water; no need for a dump right now.
All right.
[Try to maintain attitude 0 (roll), 180 (pitch), and 0 (yaw) during this mission]
13, Houston. We want you to disable the Auto on RCS Charlie. And we have a procedure for getting power from the LM we'd like you to copy down.
Okay [Lovell: Stand by, Jack.] That sounds like good news.
Okay, Jack. About how long is it?

It's not a very long procedure, Fred. We figure we've got about 15 minutes worth of power left in the Command Module, so we want you to start getting over in the LM and getting some power on that. And, you ready to copy your procedure?
Go ahead.

Okay. In the CSM on panel 5, circuit breakers LM Power 1 and 2, Open. Then LM Power switch, reset and release. In the LM, on panel 11 and panel 16, Translunar Bus Tie. Both circuit breakers Close. On panel 16, circuit breaker Ascent ECA Control, Close. On 16, Descent ECA Control, Close. On panel 14, put your Bat 5 Normal feed On. BATs 1, 2, 3, and 4 Low Voltage taps, On. Bat 5 Normal feed, Off. Ascent ECA Control, Open. You copy?
Okay. In the CSM, on panel 5, we want CB LM Power 1 and 2, Open. Then the LM Power switch to reset, release.
[F4 to switch to LM] In the LM, panels 11 and 16, X Lunar Bus Tie breakers closed. On panel 16, the Ascent ECA Control closed; the Descent ECA Control closed.
On panel 14, Bat 5 Normal feed On, followed by BATS 1, 2, 3, and 4 Low Voltage taps On. Then Bat 5 Normal feed Off. Then Ascent ECA Control breaker Open.
And, 13, Houston. As a final effort here, we would like you to turn on the fans in tank 2. Over.
O2 tanks - fans in tank 2 are on.
Roger.
13, Houston. We'd like you to start making your way over to the LM now.
Fred and Jim are in the LM.
Okay, Jack. Thank you.
And, Jack, I got LM power on.
I have an activation procedure. I'd like you to copy it down.
It's just four lines. Go to Activation 1, do step 3. Go to Activation 11, omit step 1. Do Activation 12, and then go to Activation 13 and do step 1. Do you copy?
Okay. Is that Activation 1? Do step 3.
Activation 11, omit step 1, do the rest.
Do Activation 12 and Activation 13, step 1.
Check volts, Bat 1.
Check volts, Bat 2.
Check volts, Bat 3.
Check volts, Bat 4.
Check volts, CDR BUS.
Check volts, LMP BUS.
That's all correct.
And, Jim, when you get to the end of that procedure, we'd also like to have you put the Demand Regs to Cabin.
Demand Regs to Cabin. Roger.

[In the CM] Jack, this is Houston. We want you to keep the IMU up and keep the lights on so you can see in there, and leave battery off - battery A off and, at the appropriate time, we'll put it on Main A. And we're going to keep the IMU up so as we can get a coarse align in the LM.
All right. Real good. Right now, we're charging battery A. Do you want to discontinue that?
Let's discontinue the charge on battery A, Jack.
Okay, Jack. I discontinued charge on battery A. You give me the call and I'll turn Bus Tie AC on.
Roger. And we want you to keep the lights up and the IMU on.
Okay.
And, 13, this is Houston. I've got another procedure for the LM. A short one.
Okay. Ready to copy, Jack.

Okay. On panel 11, we'd like you to close the LGC DSKY circuit breaker. Then we want you to go to Activation 25; do steps 1, 2, and 3. Then go to Activation 30, and that will give us a docked IMU coarse align. Over.
Ok, then the ACT-25 - PGNS TURN-ON & SELF TEST.
[Check CDR bus Voltage]
[Check LMP bus Voltage]
On the DSKY, Key V35E - lights test.
[Key V37E 00E]
And in the LM, let's go to panel 11 and close the Suit Fan circuit breaker and get suit fan 1 cranked up.
Okay. Panel 11, close Suit Fan circuit breaker, and we'll get the suit fan cranked up.
And, Jack, in the CSM, go to Bypass on the radiators and turn your Glycol Pump off.
Okay. Pull the Bypass; Glycol Pump going off. [Switch to the CSM]
And, 13, in the CSM, we want to verify that all the fuel cell pumps are off, and we want to have you turn off the O2 fans in the tank 2.
Okay. Tank 2 fans going off. Okay. That leaves me with tank 1 fans on the tank 1 heaters on. [That's affirm.] Fuel cell 2 pump going off now.
Okay. And, Jack, how do you read from Aquarius?
Aquarius, Houston. Say again, please.
Okay. I was just making a Comm check here. I'm on high voltage taps.
Roger. We see them, Fred, and I'm reading you loud and clear.
Okay. Didn't think I'd be back this soon.
Okay. What next, James? Coarse align? Do it right. Take your time.
That's affirmative. And, Odyssey, we've got another configuration for you. All 16 RCS Auto Select Off. All RCS heaters off. Over.
Okay. I can verify all heaters off. Jack, I've got to keep a fairly minimum deadband until I get through this coarse align.
Roger.

[The next few instruction will aid in the IMU Coarse Align, using the same numbers as the real crew had. The procedure will work with your own numbers too (involves arithmetic) except for mission command and audio being different.]
[If you wish to use your own numbers, skip the automaneuvering in the next few steps and maintain 0, 180, 0 - you can use V16 N20E to see the data on the DSKY.]
[Key V48E and set DAP to 20001]
[Key V49E on the CM DSKY, press Roger when done.]
[Use V25E and set target attitude to 355.57, 167.78, 351.87 then press PRO, V50 should display]
[Set CMC MODE to AUTO]
[Press PRO on the DSKY to start the automaneuver]
[When the maneuver is complete, press VERB on the DSKY to freeze the data]
[Open the Crew Members > Request PADs -> LM: DOCKED IMU COARSE ALIGN form]
[In the Rc, type -2, press ROGER when ready (docking hatch index)]
[In the three CM fields, use the real values: 355.57, 167.78, 351.87 (does not need to match what N20 shows as long as its close), or use your own N20 values if you want to do the aritmetic)]
[Calculate the LM angles by following the arithmetic on the form. Results using real values are: 302.43, 347.78, 008.13]
Jim, ready to copy the Command Module angles?
Yes, ready to copy.
The Command Module angles are is 355.57, 167.78, 351.87.
Got it.
Houston. Okay. I want you to double check my arithmetic to make sure we got a good coarse align. The Roll Cal angle was minus 2 degrees. The Command Module angles were 355.57, 167.78, 351.87.
Okay, Jim. We copy the roll CAL at minus 2.0. The Command Module is 355.57, 167.78, 351.87.
Odyssey, Houston, your battery A on.
Battery A on now.
Odyssey, Houston. We'd like you to, on your Comm configuration, go to Primary Power Amp Off, Low Bit Rate, and Down Voice Backup. Over.
And, Aquarius, we need your Suit Gas Diverter to Cabin.
Houston. I've gone to Primary Power Amplifier, Off, Low Bit Rate, Down Voice Backup.
All right. You got it.
Okay, let us complete the coarse align. [Key V41 N20E]
[Key +30243E to insert 302.43 into R1. R1 is the desired LM outer gimbal. If you want to use your own numbers, key these instead as we go through the coarse align procedure.]
[Key +34778E to insert 347.78 into R2. R2 is the desired LM inner gimbal.]
[Key +00813E to insert 008.13 into R3. R3 is the desired LM middle gimbal.]
Aquarius, your arithmetic looks good on the coarse align, there.
Okay, NO ATT, the IMU is aligning.
Okay.
[Key V40 N20E to reset the NO ATT flag]
Okay, ZERO CDU is done, NO ATT off.
Okay, Jack, key V06 N22 and press ENTER on my mark.
Roger, ready for your mark.
[Key V06 N20 but do not press ENTER. Press ROGER when you are ready to press ENTER]
Three, Two, One, MARK!
Houston, Aquarius.
Go ahead, Aquarius.
Here are the gimbal angles. Command module, 356.69, 163.42, 346.67. Aquarius is 302.26, 345.92, 011.79. Over. [Your values might differ, that is OK]
Okay, Jim. I got Command Module 356.65, 163.42, 346.67. Aquarius, 302.26, 345.92, 011.78.
The LM middle gimbal is 011.79.
Odyssey, Houston. We need a command reset on your - on your Comm, and then we'd like you to power down to CMC, power down the IMU, heaters off on the IMU, but leave the battery A on.
Yeah, Jack. Did you copy down about the CMC IMU?
Command reset, which I've done. I'm about to power down the IMU, power down the CMC, turn the IMU heaters off, leave Bat A on.
That's affirm. Thank you.
[The next in-game steps will power down the computer and the IMU following the EMER POWER DOWN checklist used earlier.]
Key V48E and load 0 in left digit of R1: Take note of current DAP, change first digit to 0, and enter the whole string, then press PRO, PRO, PRO
Key V46E.
Key V37E 06E
On V50 N25E, checklist 00062 CMC PWR DN, press PRO to set computer to standby.

We've lost - The only advantage to doing it early; if we can power back - the LM back down. The only advantage doing it early is you can do a big burn now and a midcourse and then power the LM down. Otherwise, we got to keep the LM powered up clear until we get around the Moon. Plus it would be inside on the burn. I just hope the G&N hangs up on ... hangs in on this one - I'd sure hate to do that one manually.
Odyssey, Houston. Couple circuit breakers for you. On panel 276, on our Instrumentation Power Control, open CB number 3 and number 4.
Okay, Houston. Panel 276, Instrumentation out, CB-3 and CB-4 are open.
That's affirmative, Odyssey. and also get your SCS electronics package and power off, and your FDAI Power/GPI off, and your Auto JET SELECT, all 16 off.
Aquarius, we need to get your sublimator powered up, Activation page 20 and Activation page 21, step 3. Over.
Roger. Activation page 20 and Activation page 21, step 3, sublimator.
Okay, Jack. We'd like you to turn off your O2 tank 2 heaters and fans. Correction - tank 1. Turn the fans and heaters off.
And all your Rotational Control Power, Off. [In the CSM]
Rotation Control Power, Direct, and Auto goes Off.
Okay, Jack. Tell me there. We need to know when we're getting close to gimbal lock in the LM. We have no balls right now.
Okay. We want you to power up your eight-ball. We want you to get your RCS heaters on. Pressurize the RCS and open up the Main SOVs. Over.

Okay, Jack. I got two Commander FDAI breakers in, AC and DC, and the two GASTA breakers in AC and DC and next you'll want the RCS heaters all on with the - pressurize the RCS and then the Main SOVs open. And I think they're already open.
Roger. And, Freddo, get the TCA breakers in last. Please.
Roger, Jim. I'm holding open those until you give me a further word anyway. I'm just going to pressurize right now.
[On the LGC, Key V16 N20E]
Houston, Aquarius.
Stand by one, Aquarius, Odyssey. We'd like you to go Direct RCS and hold your present attitude out the window until the LM gets RCS powered up. Go ahead, Jim.
[In the CSM, set Directs to ON]

Well, that's my question. We're not - Our 16 20 doesn't match our eight-ball here. We went to FDAIs On, and we don't have our balls completely powered up. There may be a [garble] and our angles don't look the same and we don't want to go into gimbal lock.
Roger. How far are you from RCS power up - RCS pressurization?

Okay, Jack. I'm right up to where it's Master Arm, On; RCS, Fire; [Garble from multiple speakers.] both Logic Powers out [garble] goes into normal circuit-breaker [garble]. Do you want A in and then I'll fire them?
Okay, 13. You're both talking at once. One at a time, please.
Okay. Who's first?
Close Logic Power A and B, Fred, and pressurize RCS.
Go ahead, Odyssey.
Okay. I'm going to try to do the best I can. I've got a one-attitude reference I'm going to fly according to the lunar terminator.
Roger, Jack. Just maintain attitude.
[Try to manuever the CSM so that you point towards the Lunar Terminator through the window - it does not need to be accurate, just fint something and use it to maintain attitude.]
[Meanwhile in the LM]

Aquarius, Houston. We'll have to get some AC up so you can get a ball reading. Close your Bus Tie Inverter circuit breakers, all four of them on panel 11. Close your AC Bus Volt circuit breaker on panel 11. On panel 16, Inverter 2, Close. Select inverter 2. Over.
That's been completed, Jack.
Okay. The RCS is pressurized now.
Okay, Jack. Do you want us to proceed right on down the line with the RCS check-out and Activation 37 now?
Stand by, Fred.
Okay, Fred. Negative on the activation on page 37. Go on to your RCS pressurize and then get your TCA breakers in and go to PGNS attitude hold.
Okay, Jim. This is Houston. We want you to load the DAP with 30120.
[Key V48E]
Load the DAP with 30120.
[Key V21E +30120E PRO]
Complete.
Okay. We need to change that CSM weight.
Okay, Aquarius. Your CSM weight is 63400.
[Key V22E +63400E PRO]
[Return to P00 or V34 to Terminate.]
Take control of the LM. PGNS Attitude Hold.
Okay, Jim. How's the attitude control?
[Try to manuever the LM using the attitude control stick]
Okay, Jack. We've got attitude control now in the LM. We're going to try to rotate up through the bellyband.
Roger.
Odyssey, Houston. I've got a procedure for you.
Okay, Jack. Odyssey is ready to copy.

Okay, Jack. What we want you to do is close the reactants valve on fuel cell 2. Power down your inverters. Power down your battery relay bus. Battery ties, off, and pull your entry circuit breakers, entry battery circuit breakers A, B, and C.
Houston, Aquarius.
Go ahead, Aquarius.
Okay. Odyssey is completely powered down, according to the procedure that you read to Jack.
Roger; we copy. That's where we want to be, Jim.
Aquarius, Houston. I have some gyro torqueing angles for you.
Jim's got it. Go ahead with the gyro torqueing angles.
Okay. We'd like you to proceed with the fine align and your gyro torquing angles are X plus 003.30, Y plus 024.80, Z minus 015.10. Over.
Okay. We read Y as plus 024.80. We'll proceed on Activation 40 to fine align the platform.
[Key V76E]
[Key V42E]
[Wait for the IMU Fine Align to complete, then V34E to terminate]
Aquarius, Houston. Can you see any stars out the LM window?

Jim, what we want you to do is go with your current fine align and disregard the P51. What we're attempting to do is to crank up some LMS simulations to correlate what we can get out your window with what we can get out the LMS window to see if that will help us any.

Okay. I'm looking out of Fred's window. I see a lot of particles out there, but a lot of that stuff is still drifting away from us, so a lot of it is flashing in the local vicinity, and I don't recognize any constellations right now, in this particular attitude.
Okay, Jim. If that status changes, please let us know.
And, Aquarius; Houston. I've got some circuit breakers you can open to power down displays. In addition, I have a P30 maneuver PAD. Over.
Roger. Stand by, Houston. Get the CS ... get the PAD book.
Okay. Go ahead with the breakers first, Jack.
Okay, they're all on panel 11. Row 1 under AC Bus B, open Helium PQGS for Propellant Display.
On row 2, Flight Displays, open Thrust, open Mission Timer, open Range/Range Rate, Altitude/Altitude Rate, and open the AC Bus A Range Rate, Altitude/Altitude Rate.
Okay. On row 4, PGNS, Signal Strength Display.
Okay. They're all Open.
Okay. That concludes the power-down of displays. And I have a P30 PAD for you.
Okay. Go ahead.

Okay. The purpose is a pericynthion plus 2 hours DPS abort. Noun 33: 079:25:26.48; plus 1633.0, minus 0014.5, minus 0751.5; apogee not applicable, perigee is plus 0020.5; 1797.7, 8:35, 268, 264, plus 16410, minus 00145, minus 07338. COAS is NA.
[Proceed when ready]

Pericynthion plus 2 - Okay, DPS pericynthion plus 2, at 079:25:026.48; plus 1633.0, minus 0014.5, minus 0751.5; HA N slash A, HP plus 0020.5; 1797.7, 8:35, 268, 264, plus 16410, minus 00145, minus 07338
Good readback, Fred.
And, Freddo, I got some fast circuit breakers on panel 16 for you.
Okay. Go ahead.
Okay. On row 1 under Flight Displays, Systems Engineer's Crosspointer, Open.
Under RCS B, open the Temp/Press Display-Flags and PQGS/Displays.
Okay, Fred. On row 3 under Comm, open Displays and under ECS, open Displays.
Okay. And two more. In row 4 under Heaters, open Displays and under EPS, open Displays.
[Turn off the lights or dim them as much as you can]
Okay. Let's fire on the mission timer.
[Press the SYNC MET TIMERS function bubble (C to toggle) to automatically set the mission timer]
Okay. And one other thing we noticed. When you pressurized the RCS, we got an increase in pressure in the ascent tanks, and so we want to have you verify that the ascent feeds are closed.
In order to do that, on panel 11, close the Ascent Feed 1 and 2 circuit breakers on - and cycle the Parker valves, and then open the Ascent Feed circuit breakers on panel 11.
Completed, Houston.
Okay, Jim. Thank you.
And, Jack, Aquarius. What kind of return time is this maneuver given?
That puts you back in the water at 133 hours.
33, hey.
Affirm. And that's an Atlantic landing site.
Atlantic landing?
Affirmative. That's the PAD that we've given you, but we may change our mind later on. We want you to have this info for now.
Okay.
Aquarius, Houston. We've got to change the REFSMMAT to the one to which you're aligned. So we'd like to have P00 and DATA and we'll ship that up to you.
[Set LGC to P00]
Okay, you got it, Jack.
Roger. Coming up.
Aquarius, could you give us DATA please?
[Multiple speakers]...the updata link, the DUA breaker may not be in, Jack.
Okay, Fred, and close the DUA breaker.
It's in now, Jack.
Okay, Jim, and it's coming up now. Thank you.
Aquarius, Houston. We're finished with the uplink. The computer is yours. We'd like to power down the DUA, so pull the DUA circuit breaker please.
Okay. Updata link breaker is coming Open.
[This complets the mission.]

Title: MISSION 9 - THE LIFEBOAT
Description: The Command Module have had a serious issue and the crew is trying to identify what has happened, and are looking at survival options. Landing on the Moon is no longer the target.
BriefingText:
Primary objectives:
• to perform selenological inspection, survey, and sampling of
materials in a preselected region of the Fra Mauro formation;
• to deploy and activate an Apollo lunar surface experiments package;
• to further develop human capability to work in the lunar environment; and
• to obtain photographs of candidate exploration sites.
